		<td><b>CHR-ROM writes..</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I've observed some programs attempt to write to their character ROM area (that is PPU's $0000-$1FFFF address range) through $2007. Examples of this are "U-Force Test Cartridge (U)" or "1942 (JU)".
<br />
<br />My question here is: as those writes cannot be made effective, how does a NES behave on this situation?
<br />
<br />Thanks.
<br />
<br />M.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


